        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 2:21PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 221 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 5 miles north of Ozark to 4 miles south of Fern.
Movement was south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Jethro...                         Altus...
Mulberry...                       Barnes...
Watalula...                       Piney...
Toney...                          Fern...
Wiederkehr Village...             Cecil...
Lonelm...                         Ozark...
Cravens...                        Paradise...
Turners Bend...                   Denning...

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 20 and
41.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
